<br>
As he watched his brother playing among the mortals, he could not help but smile.  Apparently things in the realm of the sea had grown boring and Poseidon was in need of some recreation.  Course Zeus, personally, preferred a more intimate form of recreation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/22/01 12:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=163>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~War~</span><hr size=1> Varia growled and galloped past Hypnos. As she did so she reached down and snagged the sleeping Sartha from the ground and laid her over the back of her horse until she'd wake up and keep fighting. At the same time she gave a sharp jab with her boot to her gelding's right hip, and Blade whinnied and gave Hypnos a double-barreled kick in the back of his knees, knocking him off balance and to the ground.<br>
