<br>
Nothing was about to stop this Amazon Queen . . . <br>
<br>
Until she saw it. Hippolyte.<br>
<br>
&quot;No!&quot; She screamed as memories of past wars flooded her mind. She remembered when she lost Hippolyte once before. Her eyes turned and she saw Hera in the distance. She sighed lightly knowing Hera would watch over her athelfi.<br>
<br>
Alysia turned once more and caught sight of Fogstone sending that blasted Dragon off once more, and before the beast got anywhere near the Northern Lands, Alysia's wolves were there defending the lands.<br>
<br>
The Queen chanted a few words of the ancients and Atmah Cyane leaned her hand out placing a sheild around the sacred village that no man or beast could enter through.<br>
<br>
(Yeah see, seeing that I claim Scynthia, I'm not about to let it get burned down by a freakin Dragon. Sorry but those were not the rules of this war.)<br>
<br>
<br>
Her eyes turned once more and sawn Dawn in the distance. As she fought, she kept her eyes open upon her best friend. Sadly, she wished Livia was there fighting along side her. Now that would be a sight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/22/01 10:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=165>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: War</span><hr size=1> upon seeing Apollo get up and charge at her, she turned herself into a cloud of mist letting apollo run right through her hitting nothing but the moist mist she condenced herself into. as soon as he passed through her she regained her solid form just in time to jump on the charriot as her dragons swooped down to get her off the battle field grounds. once in the sky she muttered another spell as she flies over Apollo stalagmites and stalagtites form at the bottom of her charriot as they start to fall down upon him. <p>*~`~* Hecate goddess of Sorcery, Silver-footed Queen of the Night, One of the many who resides in Tartarus, the underworld *~`~*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/22/01 12:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=166>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Death Rains from the Sky</span><hr size=1> Apollo looked around bewildered as he whipped the black mist off of his face. His face curled in disgust, the mist tasted like bull....never mind. His head shot up as he heard the shrill cries of Hecate's dragons flying off into the afternoon sky. His eyes narrowed as he saw her mouth begin moving. A spell, surely she couldn't go one battle without one. That just wouldn't be Hecate.<br>
<br>
Apollo's body fell into attack position as his eyes shot around looking for some kind of thing to fight. Some kind of puppet of which Hecate would be master. Apollo's head turned to the left, then the right looking for some kind of mystical attacker. He found nothing. As his head turned to in front of him as a huge stalagmite fell before him, just missing his head. Apollo stumbled back as more stalagmites fell from the bottom of her ebony chariot.<br>
<br>
Jump left. Jump right. Flip back. Apollo managed to evade some of the death spikes. He flipped back and lost his footing. He slipped slamming onto his chest. Apollo spat the mud from his mouth and tried to whip it from his face, only managing to smear it. As he was getting up another one fell from the sky, luckily he rolled out of its way and stood up. Apollo jumped out of the way of another falling spike, but landed right into the line of fire for another.<br>
<br>
It sliced through the arm of his armor. Apollo's eyes widened as he looked at the gash. His eyes glazed over with rage as his gaze lifted to Hecate. Jumping into the air he called out for assistance:<br>
<br>
&quot;PELIDEUS!!!&quot; he shouted the name of his winged griffin. Just as another spike fell to the earth, Apollo was swept into the air by the winged beast. Pelideus shrieked as he ripped through the sky towards the chariot of Hecate. The griffin brought Apollo as close as he could to Hecate's death chariot. Apollo stood up, steadying himself and jumped for it.<br>
<br>
As Apollo pulled himself onboard the chariot, Pelideus flew up front and attacked her dragons. Finally in the chariot Apollo narrowed his eyes at Hecate.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let's not play dirty...Silver-footed Nurse...&quot;<br>
<br>
Apollo smirked drawing once again his sword. He was ready to actually fight Hecate, hopefully she would not run away this time. The chariot began to plunge towards earth as her dragons were distracted from keeping the chariot in the air. It was going to get very interesting, very soon.<br>
