<br>
Apollo's face then swung to the left as his other, still perfect, cheek was slapped...and HARD. Apollo almost tripped out of the chariot, but caught his footing. A hand raised to his cheek. He was too outraged to notice the outrageous smell. The twitch in his right eye grew worse as he realized the pure and excessive amount of audacity had by Hecate. Short tempered bitc...he was getting distracted.<br>
<br>
Within the grace and perfection of a hawk diving for its pray, Apollo raised his sword and plunged it into the stomach of Hecate. Not only did he plunge the sword in, he twisted it to add to her pain. He then grabbed her by the collar of her &quot;outfit&quot;( if you want to call that hideous gathering of mismatched fabrics an outfit). He gritted his teeth and practically growled.<br>
<br>
&quot;How dare you!&quot; he pushed her over the side of the chariot so she was sure to lose her balance. The only thing keeping her from falling his him holding onto her collar...oh yes, and the sword in her stomach.<br>
<br>
&quot;I will NOT, allow you to do such things to me, no matter who the hell you THINK you are. No matter what &quot;magical, whimsical, and menacing&quot; spell you can conjure up in that SICK mind of yours, you will NEVER disrespect me like that again. The matter in which you fight is despicable and uncalled for.&quot; Apollo narrowed his twitching eye at her.<br>
<br>
Grasping the grip on his sword he plunged the sword in deeper. The blood dripped from his crimson-stained cheek onto the handle of the sword.<br>
<br>
&quot;You...you....MY FACE!&quot; Apollo shrieked so loud it probably brought pain to the ears of Zeus.<br>
<br>
Apollo grew tired of this stupidity. He knew that no words, or any action of his would get through to Hecate. She was one of the most close minded, and intentionally impersonable goddesses in the Olympic family (after Eris that is). There was no use in continuing this, she could not be killed, and she would remain blinded by her ignorance for all eternity.<br>
<br>
His eyes rolled to her. He was ashamed to say the least. Gripping the collar tighter he pulled her up, allowing her to stand. Shaking his head, he pulled the sword from her stomach and whipped the blood upon her clothing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't bother me anymore Hecate. I haven't the time to waste on you any longer.&quot; was all he said before whistling to Pedieus. His stare was perhaps as Hades'. He seemed to stare through her. Apollo jumped into the air just as the griffin flew by to catch him. He ripped through the air towards the ground not even bothering to peer at the look Hecate most obviously had upon her face. She was unimportant now. He needed to let his rage settle before he was to deal with her again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxxdemeterxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xxDemeterxx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/23/01 1:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=174>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Not so fast</span><hr size=1> :*: Demeter watched from the sideline, true, she didnt want to get involved,she didnt want to pick sides, but she didsay she wanted to help eiter side if needed, and since it seemd her pettykin were doing so well, she helped Varia. Hypnos covering her in cobalts seemed very unfair considering Varia was merely a mortal. So instead of the cobalts burying her, they crumbled to small pieces the moment they touched her. Satisfied wih that, she smiled *: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenvaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QueenVaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/23/01 1:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=175>Reply</a>   </td><td v